The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 29 April is 41,889 (4,848.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 24 April, there were 123 new confirmed cases (14.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 17 April, there were 136 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 10% (13 fewer cases).
